- cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability): The paper involves probabilistic methods for encoding and decoding messages in subspace codes, which is a subfield of information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper may be relevant to networking and internet architecture as subspace codes are used in wireless communication and network coding. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper may be relevant to social and information networks as subspace codes are used in distributed storage and retrieval systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may involve algorithms and data structures for encoding and decoding messages in subspace codes.
